name: Partition
description: Base class of Cache.OrgPartition and Cache.SessionPartition. Use the subclasses to manage the cache partition for org caches and session caches.

contains(string).name: contains
contains(string).description: Returns true if the cache partition contains a cached value corresponding to the specified key.

createfullyqualifiedkey(string,string,st.name: createFullyQualifiedKey
createfullyqualifiedkey(string,string,st.signature: public static String createFullyQualifiedKey(String namespace, String partition, String key)
createfullyqualifiedkey(string,string,st.description: Generates a fully qualified key from the passed-in key components. The format of the generated key string is namespace.partition.key.

createfullyqualifiedpartition(string,str.name: createFullyQualifiedPartition
createfullyqualifiedpartition(string,str.signature: public static String createFullyQualifiedPartition(String namespace, String partition)
createfullyqualifiedpartition(string,str.description: Generates a fully qualified partition name from the passed-in namespace and partition. The format of the generated partition string is namespace.partition.

get(string).name: get
get(string).description: Returns the cached value corresponding to the specified key from the cache partition.

get(system.type,string).name: get
get(system.type,string).signature: public Object get(System.Type cacheBuilder, String key)
get(system.type,string).description: Returns the cached value corresponding to the specified key from the partition cache. Use this method if your cached value is a class that implements the CacheBuilder interface.

getavggettime().name: getAvgGetTime
getavggettime().description: Returns the average time taken to get a key from the partition, in nanoseconds.

getavgvaluesize().name: getAvgValueSize
getavgvaluesize().description: Returns the average item size for keys in the partition, in bytes.

getcapacity().name: getCapacity
getcapacity().description: Returns the percentage of cache used of the total capacity for this partition.

getkeys().name: getKeys
getkeys().description: Returns a set of all keys that are stored in the cache partition and visible to the invoking namespace.

getmaxgettime().name: getMaxGetTime
getmaxgettime().description: Returns the maximum time taken to get a key from the partition, in nanoseconds.

getmaxvaluesize().name: getMaxValueSize
getmaxvaluesize().description: Returns the maximum item size for keys in the partition, in bytes.

getmissrate().name: getMissRate
getmissrate().description: Returns the miss rate in the partition.

getname().name: getName
getname().description: Returns the name of this cache partition.

getnumkeys().name: getNumKeys
getnumkeys().description: Returns the total number of keys in the partition.

isavailable().name: isAvailable
isavailable().description: Returns true if the Salesforce session is available. Only applies to Cache.SessionPartition. The session cache isn’t available when an active session isn’t present, such as in asynchronous Apex or code called by asynchronous Apex. For example, if batch Apex causes an Apex trigger to execute, the session cache isn’t available in the trigger because the trigger runs in asynchronous context.

put(string,object).name: put
put(string,object).signature: public void put(String key, Object value)
put(string,object).description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the cache partition. The put method can write only to the cache in your org’s namespace.

put(string,object,cache.visibility).name: put
put(string,object,cache.visibility).signature: public void put(String key, Object value, cache.Visibility visibility)
put(string,object,cache.visibility).description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the cache partition and sets the cached value’s visibility.

put(string,object,integer).name: put
put(string,object,integer).signature: public void put(String key, Object value, Integer ttlSecs)
put(string,object,integer).description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the cache partition and sets the cached value’s lifetime.

put(string,object,integer,cache.visibili.name: put
put(string,object,integer,cache.visibili.signature: public void put(String key, Object value, Integer ttlSecs, cache.Visibility visibility, Boolean immutable)
put(string,object,integer,cache.visibili.description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the cache partition. This method also sets the cached value’s lifetime, visibility, and whether it can be overwritten by another namespace.

remove(string).name: remove
remove(string).description: Deletes the cached value corresponding to the specified key from this cache partition.

remove(system.type,string).name: remove
remove(system.type,string).signature: public Boolean remove(System.Type cacheBuilder, String key)
remove(system.type,string).description: Deletes the cached value corresponding to the specified key from the partition cache. Use this method if your cached value is a class that implements the CacheBuilder interface.

validatecachebuilder(system.type).name: validateCacheBuilder
validatecachebuilder(system.type).description: Validates that the specified class implements the CacheBuilder interface.

validatekey(boolean,string).name: validateKey
validatekey(boolean,string).signature: public static void validateKey(Boolean isDefault, String key)
validatekey(boolean,string).description: Validates a cache key. This method throws a Cache.InvalidParamException if the key is not valid. A valid key is not null and contains alphanumeric characters.

validatekeyvalue(boolean,string,object).name: validateKeyValue
validatekeyvalue(boolean,string,object).signature: public static void validateKeyValue(Boolean isDefault, String key, Object value)
validatekeyvalue(boolean,string,object).description: Validates a cache key and ensures that the cache value is non-null. This method throws a Cache.InvalidParamException if the key or value is not valid. A valid key is not null and contains alphanumeric characters.

validatekeys(boolean,set).name: validateKeys
validatekeys(boolean,set).signature: public static void validateKeys(Boolean isDefault, Set <String>)
validatekeys(boolean,set).description: Validates the specified cache keys. This method throws a Cache.InvalidParamException if the key is not valid. A valid key is not null and contains alphanumeric characters.

validatepartitionname(string).name: validatePartitionName
validatepartitionname(string).description: Validates the partition name — for example, that it is not null.
